## Intro

On April 28th, a massive power outage in Spain reminded us just how fragile our digital dependencies are. No electricity meant no access to online tools, platforms, or even basic infrastructure. It wasn’t just a blackout — it was a wake-up call.

We rely heavily on complex, expensive systems to do things we could often do ourselves — if only the tools we used were simpler and more accessible.

This is about removing blockers. About reducing the complexity of what you need in order to create. Because when you reduce that, you gain independence. Flexibility. And a deep satisfaction from building rather than just consuming.

